.TH man 1 "23 February 2023" "0.0" "simple shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B simple shell
- execute keyboard commands from the terminal
.SH SYNONSIS
.B ./hsh
 ... [COMMAND] [OPTION] [ARGUMENT]
 .SH DESCRIPTION
 Simple Shell executes commands taken from standard input and shows the results on standard output.
 .SH OPTIONS
 various commands have options, such as the option '-l' for 'ls'  which shows the directory contents in long form
 .SH ARGUMENTS
 commands take arguments such as filenames
 .SH INVOCATION
 Simple Shell is invoked by entering './' plus whatever it has been compiled to.
 .SH ENVIRONMENT
 Simple Shell's environment starts as the same as shell and user calling it, but can be changed.
 .SH BUGS
 There are limitations, such as the absence of wildcards
 .SH AUTHORS
 Cliff Omanyo and Boniface Muchendu
